   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "Each registration is individually trivial — a form and a few thousand euros — so none makes a risk list organized by 'big' instruments. The kill mechanism is their serialization against a fixed 12-month window, which only becomes visible when someone builds the compliance Gantt chart against the sales plan.",
 "falsifier": "A counsel-built compliance timeline showing all CE-7 registrations (EAR, LUCID, national WEEE equivalents, EORI, Swiss importer/SENS setup) are completable in parallel within 90 days pre-launch.",
 "likelihoodRationale": "The registrations are legally mandatory and their lead times are documented administrative facts; the base rate of hardware entrants underestimating multi-country EPR/WEEE sequencing is high. Uncertainty is only whether the venture has quietly already started them. [evidence revision: Evidence solidly confirms the mechanism's core factual premises — multi-month WEEE lead times, mandatory pre-sale registration, a broader-than-modeled register stack, foreign authorized-representative requirements, and Switzerland's distinct non-EU regime. This raises confidence in the serialization dynamic slightly above the base-rate prior. The residual uncertainty is unchanged: whether the venture has already started these registrations (unobservable here) and whether use of representatives/agents can compress timelines. EORI being fast is noted but is not the binding constraint. Modest upward revision to 0.55.]"
